cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the use of mesh networking and blockchain technologies in the telecommunications industry, specifically for creating economically sustainable wireless mesh networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of blockchain for transparency and accountability, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of smart contracts and economic coordination, which could fall under the categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the use of cryptocurrencies, which could fall under the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
